U.S. Treasury Department Schedule for Thursday, April 21

-- B y   V i n c e n t   D e l   G i u d i c e
-- 
2011-04-21T12:03:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/u-s-treasury-department-schedule-for-thursday-april-21.html
The following is a reformatted
version of the U.S. Treasury Department’s daily release on the
schedule for Secretary Timothy F. Geithner and other officials:  On Thursday morning, Deputy Secretary Wolin will join
Secretary of Education Arne Duncan at the Department of
Education at an awards ceremony to recognize high-scoring
students in the National Financial Capability Challenge. The
Challenge, which includes a voluntary online exam for high
school students, helps teach young Americans about saving,
budgeting, investing, and other important skills critical to
building a strong financial future. The awards ceremony will
take place at a meeting of the President’s Advisory Council on
Financial Capability. This event is open press.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Del Giudice in  Washington  
 vdelgiudice@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at   cwellisz@bloomberg.net  